RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANGOLA VACATION pressed the early pace, forwardly placed throughout, dueled down the final stretch and drove clear before the wire. MR. NUMERO UNO went to the front, came in around the first turn, causing tight quarters for inside rivals, showed speed throughout, but was no match late for the winner. DREWNANIMOUS raced within contention, steadied around the first turn, getting in tight quarters and followed the top two to the wire. UNCLE CHAN raced within striking distance, got in tight quarters around the first turn, bobbled, made a mild bid, but was no factor. MUSTBELIEVE raced near the middle of the field, came around the final turn on the out side and put forth an even effort. VALID EARLY lacked early speed, showed late interest, but was no threat. CRAZY MUGGS void of early speed and was never close. D'FESTIVE CAT always raced near the back and showed little. TRUVY'S BANDIT pressed the early pace and made a steady retreat. CORTE trailed throughout and was outrun. THE JOCKEY OF #1 UNCLE CHAN LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST #3 ANGOLA VACATION AND #4 MR. NUMERO UNO FOR INTERFERENCE ENTERING THE FIRST TURN. AFTER VIEWING REPLAYS STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED #4 FROM 2ND AND PLACED HIM FOURTH.
